---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Product Managers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Product Managers working internationally, covering product management careers abroad, tech industry, and global product leadership opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Product Managers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Product Managers working abroad, building products internationally, and pursuing careers across technology companies and product organizations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/product-manager-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/product-manager-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Product Manager Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Product Managers define what gets built and why. They bridge business strategy, user needs, and technical execution to create products that solve real problems. PMs own the product vision, roadmap, and outcomes while coordinating cross-functional teams.
      </p>
      <p>
        International product management opportunities exist through global technology companies, multinational corporations building digital products, startups with distributed teams, and the remote-friendly nature of product work enabling flexible arrangements.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Product Managers working abroad across technology companies and product organizations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Product Managers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'High-pressure decision making', typical: 'Important to include' },
          { need: 'Vision care', why: 'Screen-intensive work', typical: 'Should be comprehensive' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Desk-based profession', typical: 'Consider carefully' },
          { need: 'Remote work coverage', why: 'Distributed teams common', typical: 'If remote arrangement' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Career protection', typical: 'Review carefully' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Decision-Making Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Product Managers make consequential decisions daily about what to build. Wrong decisions waste engineering time and can impact business outcomes significantly. This accountability creates ongoing pressure that benefits from mental health support.
      </p>
      <p>
        Balancing stakeholder demands, user needs, and technical constraints requires constant negotiation. Managing conflicting priorities while maintaining product vision is cognitively demanding. Understanding these pressures helps identify coverage priorities.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Work Prevalence</h3>
      <p>
        Product management translates well to remote work, with many companies offering distributed options. This flexibility creates international opportunities but also insurance complexity. Understanding coverage implications of remote arrangements important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Technology Companies</h3>
      <p>
        FAANG and major tech. Tech benefits comprehensive. Core product roles. Big tech offers resources and structure.
      </p>

      <h3>Startups</h3>
      <p>
        Early-stage companies. Startup benefits variable. High ownership and impact. Startups offer breadth of experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Growth Companies</h3>
      <p>
        Series B-D stage. Benefits improving. Scaling challenges. Growth stage offers momentum.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise Software</h3>
      <p>
        B2B product companies. Enterprise benefits solid. Complex customer needs. Enterprise offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Consumer Products</h3>
      <p>
        B2C companies. Benefits vary by size. User-centric focus. Consumer offers visible impact.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Product Managers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across technology companies and product organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Product Manager Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Track record most valued. Shipped products demonstrate capability. Domain expertise valuable. Experience trumps credentials.
      </p>

      <h3>Education</h3>
      <p>
        MBA common but not required. Technical background helpful. Diverse paths to PM. Background less important than results.
      </p>

      <h3>Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        Product certifications exist. Pragmatic Marketing, AIPMM. Less weight than experience. Certifications supplement track record.
      </p>

      <h3>Portfolio</h3>
      <p>
        Case studies valuable. Launch results documentation. Before/after metrics. Portfolio demonstrates impact.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Cognitive Load</h3>
      <p>
        Constant context switching. Multiple stakeholders and projects. Decision fatigue. Mental health support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Meeting Intensity</h3>
      <p>
        Heavily meeting-dependent role. Stakeholder alignment sessions. Sprint ceremonies. Meeting fatigue common.
      </p>

      <h3>Screen Time</h3>
      <p>
        Documentation and analysis. Roadmapping tools. Communication platforms. Vision care important.
      </p>

      <h3>Work Hours</h3>
      <p>
        Launch periods intense. Generally manageable otherwise. On-call expectations vary. Work-life balance achievable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Strategy</h3>
      <p>
        Vision and roadmap ownership. Prioritization frameworks. Market analysis. Strategy sets direction.
      </p>

      <h3>Execution</h3>
      <p>
        Sprint coordination. Launch management. Cross-functional alignment. Execution delivers results.
      </p>

      <h3>Communication</h3>
      <p>
        Stakeholder updates. Team alignment. Customer feedback loops. Communication enables progress.
      </p>

      <h3>Metrics</h3>
      <p>
        KPI ownership. A/B testing. Performance analysis. Metrics demonstrate value.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>International Opportunities</h3>
      <p>
        Global tech company roles. Remote product positions. International product launches. Coverage must accommodate flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior PM to Director. VP of Product track. CPO trajectory. Founder path common. Multiple options available.
      </p>

      <h3>Compensation</h3>
      <p>
        Competitive tech salaries. Equity significant in startups. Geographic variation. Market generally favorable.
      </p>

      <h3>AI Impact</h3>
      <p>
        AI products expanding. PM skills for AI needed. Field evolving rapidly. Adaptation and learning essential.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a product manager considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Skills transfer globally. Remote options expanding. Tech companies facilitate mobility. International experience valued.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I work remotely internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Many PM roles support remote. Time zone alignment important. Tax and legal complexity. Verify coverage for location.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is PM stress significant?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Decision pressure real. Stakeholder management challenging. Launch stress peaks. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do tech companies provide good coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Generally excellent benefits. Major tech competitive. Startups variable. Verify specific provisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is technical background necessary?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Helpful but not required. Technical PMs valued. Business background works. Domain expertise matters.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong demand continues. Every tech company needs PMs. AI creating new opportunities. Positive long-term trajectory.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by understanding your employer's coverage provisions and remote work policies. Tech companies typically provide comprehensive benefits. Verify mental health provisions given decision-making pressure. Consider coverage implications of distributed work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Product Managers shape what technology gets built. Your coverage should support flexible, global careers—addressing professional demands, accommodating remote options, and protecting your health across product leadership roles worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Product Management Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across technology companies and product organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
